Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
eco_opt_ir_aggressor(25.10)                        eco_opt_ir_aggressor(25.10)

Name
       eco_opt_ir_aggressor

Syntax
       eco_opt_ir_aggressor

       [-help]

       [-create_margin]

       -domain_threshold <value>

       [-effort {high||medium||low}]

       [-margin <value>]

       [-noEcoRoute]

       [-save_margin]

       -state_directory <directoryname>

       [-watch_box <filename>]

       The eco_opt_ir_aggressor command optimizes the IR drop violations based
       on  the  user-specified  IR drop threshold. The IR drop impact from the
       aggressors will be analyzed and then optimized by aggressor sizing.

       You must specify this command after running the analyze_rail command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each eco_opt_ir_aggressor parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man eco_opt_ir_aggressor.

       -create_margin
              Specifies to create margin for sizing candidates. This parameter
              is  specified  with the -margin parameter. If you do not specify
              -margin, instead specify only -create_margin, then  the  default
              margin of 0.02 ns will be used.

       -domain_threshold <value>
              Specifies  the minimum allowed voltage for the domain being ana-
              lyzed. The value will be in percentage. This parameter  behavior
              is same as the set_rail_analysis_domain -threshold parameter.

       -effort {high||medium||low}
              Specifies the effort level for running signoffOptDesign/opt_sig-
              noff.

              * low - specifies to perform standalone signoffOptDesign.

              * medium  or  high  -  separates  the  aggressors into different
                groups based on their Total Instance Voltage Drop (TIV) impact
                and invokes signoffOptDesign multiple times.

       -margin <value>
              Specifies the margin value for fixing IR violations. This  para-
              meter is specified with the -create_margin parameter. The speci-
              fied  margin  is used to create timing margin for the aggressors
              that cannot be downsized. If you do not specify -margin, instead
              specify only -create_margin, then the default margin of 0.02  ns
              will be used.

              The value of margin is in ns.

       -noEcoRoute
              Specifies  to skip ECO routing after sizing the aggressors. This
              parameter allows you to customize your ecoRoute option.

       -save_margin
              Specifies to save the margin for the next run of IR-ECO.

       -state_directory <directoryname>
              Specifies the top-level state directory that is generated by the
              dynamic IR drop analysis. This state directory contains analysis
              of all nets associated with the power domain. This is the output
              directory in which the results of the  analyze_rail  command  is
              stored (for example, core_25C_dynamic_1).

       -watch_box <filename>
              Specifies  a  file  containing the list of regions, wherein only
              the instances inside these regions will be  reported  for  opti-
              mization. You can write multiple regions in the file.

              The format of the file is:

              {{x1,y1}{x2,y2}}

              {{x3,y3}{x4,y4}}

Examples
              *

                The  following command specifies to optimize IR drop violation
                and reduce the IR drop aggressor impact:

                eco_opt_ir_aggressor    -state_directory     dynVecLessRailRe-
                sults_ori221/latest -effort high -domain_threshold 0.08

              * The following command specifies to skip ECO routing when opti-
                mizing IR drop violations:

                eco_opt_ir_aggressor  -state_directory RailBeforeWorstavg/lat-
                est -domain_threshold $TH -effort high -noEcoRoute

